      "title": "LOOP",
      "type": "poem",
      "description": "",
      "content": "I tied my laces twice,\r\nAnd both times,\r\nThe knot untied itself before I could stand,\r\nAs if the floor refused to let me leave.\r\nHolding me in place.\r\nThe time seemed to lag.\r\nAn endless loop.\r\nYet frozen in time",
